videos.headline: Jackson to Bonnafon puts the Cardinals in field goal range
videos.description: Lamar Jackson connects with Reggie Bonnafon for 21 yards to put Louisville in position for a field goal.

videos.headline: Newsome goes 54 yards to put the Tar Heels in the red zone
videos.description: Chazz Surratt pitches to Dazz Newsome, who takes it 54 yards to put UNC in the red zone.

videos.headline: Surratt finds Fritts for a North Carolina TD
videos.description: Chazz Surratt completes to Brandon Fritts for a 1-yard touchdown to put the Tar Heels in the lead.

videos.headline: Jackson's TD pass gives Louisville the lead
videos.description: Lamar Jackson finds Dez Fitzpatrick for a 9-yard touchdown to put the Cardinals in the lead.

videos.headline: North Carolina stuffs Jackson to force a field goal
videos.description: Lamar Jackson is sacked on the 10-yard line by North Carolina.

videos.headline: Jackson's grab shifts the momentum for the Tar Heels
videos.description: Chazz Surratt connects with Thomas Jackson for 37 yards to put UNC in Louisville territory.

videos.headline: Fritts' second TD gives UNC the lead
videos.description: Chazz Surratt completes to Brandon Fritts for a 5-yard touchdown to put the Tar Heels ahead.

videos.headline: Jackson's 75-yard TD pass puts Louisville ahead
videos.description: Lamar Jackson completes to Jaylen Smith for a 75-yard touchdown to give the Cardinals the lead in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Greenard forces fumble on Surratt sack for a 30-yard loss
videos.description: Chazz Surratt is sacked by Jonathan Greenard  and fumbles the ball for a loss of 30 yards.

videos.headline: Jackson escapes sack for 1st down
videos.description: Lamar Jackson spins out of a sack and runs seven yards for a first down.

videos.headline: Petrino discusses Louisville's first half
videos.description: Louisville head coach Bobby Petrino talks about movement on offensive and what adjustments have to be made on defense for the second half.

videos.headline: Fedora on "big mistakes" to change for the second half
videos.description: North Carolina head coach Larry Fedora highlights the changes his team has to make for the second half.

videos.headline: Jackson's 43-yard TD run extends Louisville's lead
videos.description: Lamar Jackson runs it up the middle for 43 yards and a touchdown in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Ratliff-Williams returns kickoff for 94-yard TD for UNC
videos.description: North Carolina's Anthony Ratliff-Williams returns the kick for a 94-yard touchdown to cut Louisville's lead to 27-21.

videos.headline: Jackson snags TD to help UNC reclaim lead
videos.description: Brandon Harris completes to Thomas Jackson in the end zone for a touchdown to put UNC in the lead in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Jackson's fourth TD puts Cardinals back in the lead
videos.description: Lamar Jackson runs for a 4-yard touchdown to put Louisville back in the lead in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: Dawkins stiff arms Sails to the ground
videos.description: Seth Dawkins stiff arms K.J. Sails to the ground on 21-yard reception for a first down.

videos.headline: Jackson's fifth TD widens Louisville's lead
videos.description: Lamar Jackson finds Dez Fitzpatrick for a 30-yard touchdown to extend the Cardinals' lead.

videos.headline: Williams' 74-yard run puts the Cardinals in the red zone
videos.description: Malik Williams runs for 74 yards for a Louisville first down to put them in the red zone.

videos.headline: Jackson runs 11 yards for his sixth TD of the game
videos.description: Lamar Jackson rushes 11 yards for his third rushing touchdown of the game, extending Louisville's lead.

videos.headline: Carter runs for a 1-yard TD
videos.description: Michael Carter punches it in from 1 yard to close the gap.

videos.headline: Petrino all smiles after getting the win
videos.description: Louisville head coach Bobby Petrino discusses how his team responded to UNC in the second half in the Cardinals' 47-35 win.

videos.headline: Jackson reflects on Louisville win
videos.description: Lamar Jackson talks about the change in his maturity this season on and off the field and next week's game with Clemson
